channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Hurricane Helene live updates: 10 dead, millions without power
item.description: Helene made landfall in Florida's Big Bend region Thursday night as a massive Category 4 hurricane -- the strongest hurricane to make landfall in the Big Bend on record.

item.title: Netanyahu, at UN, vows that Israel will keep 'degrading Hezbollah' until its objectives are met
Key U.S. inflation gauge shows prices continued cooling in August
item.description: Grocery costs barely rose last month, according to Friday's report, and energy costs dropped 0.8%, led by cheaper gasoline.

item.title: Dame Maggie Smith, venerable British actress, dies at 89
item.description: Maggie Smith, a lauded British actress who starred in "Harry Potter" and "Downton Abbey" has died at the age of 89.

item.title: Couple caught performing sex act under coats on easyJet flight
Ex-intelligence chief jailed for "aggravated torture" of journalist
item.description: Enrique Ariza was convicted of "persecution, harassment" and other crimes against Claudia Julieta Duque, the prosecutor's office said.

item.title: LIVE: ABC News Live
item.description: 24/7 coverage of breaking news and live events

item.title: Bosses at Tesla's German Gigafactory are reportedly knocking on some workers' doors when they're at home sick
Hurricane Helene pounds Florida, FEMA administrator on recovery
item.description: Hurricane Helene left damage behind in Tallahassee, Florida, and other areas close to the Gulf of Mexico. Tom Hanson reports. Also, FEMA Administrator Deanne Criswell joins CBS News with more on federal response for those affected.

item.title: WATCH: Residents and dog rescued from Hurricane Helene floodwaters
item.description: Rescue crews pulled three people and a dog from floodwaters in Hillsborough County, Florida, on Thursday, as Hurricane Helene hit the region.

item.title: See homes float away in storm surge
Eric Adams set to be arraigned on federal charges
item.description: New York City Mayor Eric Adams is set to be arraigned Friday on federal charges that include bribery, conspiracy and campaign finance charges. CBS News' Anna Schecter reports.

item.title: Gov. Gavin Newsom deals blow to reparations effort in California
item.description: Gov. Gavin Newsom deals a legislative blow to the groundbreaking reparations effort in Californa.

item.title: Holocaust scholar to discuss his conclusion that Gaza campaign constitutes genocide
Naomi Campbell banned from running U.K. charity over "serious misconduct"
item.description: U.K. regulators found "serious misconduct" by Naomi Campbell's Fashion for Relief charity, disqualifying her from running a charity in Britain for five years.
